    "title" : "Why does this substitution not work with HOCON",
    "body" : "<p>I am trying to use a HOCON config &amp; the <code>include</code> keyword to be able to overwrite environment variables when running a java server locally. File structure looks like this</p>\n<hr />\n<p>local.conf</p>\n<pre><code>include &quot;app.conf&quot;\n</code></pre>\n<p>app.conf</p>\n<pre><code>z {\n  useSecret: ${SECRET}\n}\n</code></pre>\n<hr />\n<p>Can overwrite this environment variable from the same file no problem</p>\n<p>app.conf</p>\n<pre><code>SECRET: &quot;fooBar&quot;\nz {\n  useSecret: ${SECRET}\n}\n</code></pre>\n<hr />\n<p>But from a different file it generates a <code>Could not resolve substitution to a value: ${SECRET}</code></p>\n<p>local.conf</p>\n<pre><code>SECRET: &quot;fooBar&quot;\ninclude &quot;app.conf&quot;\n</code></pre>\n<p>app.conf</p>\n<pre><code>z {\n  useSecret: ${SECRET}\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>What am I doing wrong?</p>\n",
