    "answer_id" : 79697354,
    "question_id" : 79694518,
    "body" : "<p>I ended up finding a solution that worked around the original problem. Instead of including environment overrides in the top level file, I ended up doing an <code>include</code> in <code>app.conf</code> to a file dedicated to environment var overrides</p>\n<p>EG:</p>\n<p><strong>local.conf</strong></p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>include &quot;app.conf&quot;\n\n# some other stuff\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>app.conf</strong></p>\n<pre><code>include &quot;envoverride.conf&quot;\nz {\n  useSecret: ${SECRET}\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>envoverride.conf</strong></p>\n<pre><code>SECRET: &quot;fooBar&quot;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Didn't really get to the root of my original problem but worked for me</p>\n",
